summary:
I’m a multi-disciplinary designer with 7+ years of experience. I have experience working with branding,   UI/UX, type design, illustration design, publication design, packaging, emails, info-graphics, video and social.  I am currently work as a global graphic designer at ASML, supporting the employer branding team.
I have a B.Sc. (with Honors) in Applied Sciences and Arts from the German University in Cairo. My Project branding the Grand Egyptian Museum won two international awards; the first ‘Gold A’ Design Award’, as
part of the 2019/2020 A’ Design Award and Competition. The second ‘German Design Awards’ Winner for 2021 in
the category Excellent Communications Design (Corporate Identity).
Award link: https://competition.adesignaward.com/design.php?ID=100110

Whether an old or a new business owner, franchise owner, marketer, chef, supplier or a photographer/food stylist, This event is for you if you are serious about becoming much better at this business.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Rana', 'last_name': 'Gaber', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Global Graphic Designer @ ASML'}]}, {'title': 'Branding the Grand Egyptian Museum', 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, 'description': 'https://www.behance.net/gallery/26501779/Branding-The-Grand-Egyptian-Museum

In my project I am creating a brand identity and a visual language. I believe that the Egyptian Museum needs a strong brand identity that communicates their new vision and mission. I am trying to use hieroglyphs in the logotype and in the signage system to reflect the Ancient Egyptian culture and style. I want people to be introduced to hieroglyphs and get used to them through the new identity. For me a good design is not just pleasing to the eye, but also is a design that changes a perception, behavior, or an attitude.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Rana', 'last_name': 'Gaber', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Global Graphic Designer @ ASML'}]}, {'title': 'Re_branding EgyptAir', 'date': {'start': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}}, 'description': 'https://www.behance.net/gallery/21154691/Re-branding-EgyptAir 

It is a well-known fact that the official airline of any nation is one of the first markers people around the world identify with. Some of the biggest names in aviation such as Emirates Airlines, British Airways, Lufthansa and Qatar Airways, have arguably acted as better ambassadors to their countries than most ambassadors deployed around the world. It is a testament to a people’s determination and a sign of an advanced civilized state. Design is a very important and crucial aspect that affects our daily lives. It creates communication channels between people and different variables. Design affects the society and the culture and vice versa. To add to this, it represents the political, economical, cultural, and environmental circumstances. It is well known that design is related to problem solving and the designer’s job description is to solve problems that face customers, users, and the public. nowadays design is not anymore limited to problem solving it goes beyond this stage. In our modern society design is used as a communication tool, to create a visual representation for an idea or a message. Graphic design is not only about type, image, space, and alignment. Its about creative solutions.
